Martin Odegaard: &ldquo;This was my decision. Real Madrid want what&rsquo;s best for me and they respected me. They want me to be happy and progress as a player.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Sergio Reguilon: &ldquo;A bit of sadness leaving but knowing that one day I can succeed there is great. It is increasingly complicated because the competition in football is greater every time. A youngster coming up is unusual &amp; it remains difficult. I hope to be there at some point.&rdquo;

Juan Carlos Restrepo, James Rodriguez&rsquo;s stepfather: &ldquo;I don't know if James is closer to Napoli or Atletico, but he knows Madrid already and he has a home in Spain.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Juan Carlos Restrepo, James Rodriguez&rsquo;s stepfather: &ldquo;You have to decide where you want to be. It's great that coaches of great clubs who have won everything in the game, want him.&quot;

Napoli President Aurelio De Laurentiis: &ldquo;James Rodriguez? We&rsquo;ve not given up, but in order to break the ice we need Real Madrid to consider that rather than have an unhappy player sitting around, they should send him out to play. Perhaps on loan.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Napoli President Aurelio De Laurentiis: &ldquo;I read a lot of stories that are untrue&hellip; I don&rsquo;t talk to Florentino Perez about James, as we have (director of sport) Giuntoli and an agent-friend of James, who is also our friend (Jorge Mendes), so we don&rsquo;t need to talk to Florentino.&rdquo;

